422	avalon_20251201_004734	proposal	100400	Alice	good	\N	Structurally, there is exactly one evil in {Charlie, Diana} from the failed Mission 2, and exactly one evil in {Bob, Eve} from the clean Mission 3. Any team of three with me must therefore be me plus one from each pair, or me plus both from one pair. A team of me–Bob–Eve is guaranteed to include exactly one evil (since it takes both from {Bob, Eve}), so it can never be an all-good team. In contrast, a mixed team of me–Bob–Charlie (one from {Charlie, Diana} and one from {Bob, Eve}) has a live possibility of being fully good if Charlie and Bob are the goods in their respective pairs.\n\nTable behavior also fits this: Charlie has consistently framed Diana as the more likely culprit from Mission 2 and avoided putting her back on, which is what I’d expect from good if Diana is evil. Bob’s preference for Alice–Charlie–Bob aligns with that same read. Meanwhile, Diana and Eve are aligned on pushing Alice–Bob–Eve, the configuration that is mathematically forced to contain exactly one evil. That pattern is more consistent with at least one of Diana/Eve being evil and trying to steer us toward a guaranteed-mixed team. Putting this together, the highest-probability all-good team given both the mission outcomes and the discussion is Alice–Bob–Charlie.	[-0.01797842,-0.041803,-0.020910835,-0.054701313,-0.008691681,0.0049906303,0.018584218,-0.056538876,0.01323313,0.064584486,-0.028362669,-0.026380887,0.07455594,-0.056754593,0.011610274,0.050333478,0.008975923,0.035260886,-0.055532455,0.041982293,-0.08255934,-0.116800964,-0.015569295,-0.025447337,-0.075353995,0.08611826,-0.032146733,0.0041170293,-0.017214814,-0.14844574,-0.030961243,0.053958002,0.027431905,0.04797681,-0.024964657,0.019393545,-0.026118087,-0.0033383213,-0.0020822869,0.027771002,-0.035806075,-0.030638672,-0.01229315,-0.040225912,-0.09100109,0.022484729,-0.039813954,0.007448874,0.024525262,-0.10833892,-0.019387592,0.03543658,0.01615739,0.044690363,0.059417035,0.0