414	avalon_20251201_003138	proposal	100401	Charlie	good	\N	Mission 3’s fail on the 2-player team of Alice + me means, from my perspective as a known-good Charlie, that Alice is definitively evil. That leaves the second evil among Bob, Diana, and Eve. The push from Alice and Eve to lock in a Diana+Eve core feels like an attempt to auto-clear Eve off a single 3-player success (Mission 2), which is exactly the kind of spot an evil can safely hide in. Diana and I both pushed back against auto-locking Eve and instead favored a Diana+Bob core, which is a much more cautious good-aligned approach. Between the remaining options, Eve’s insistence on reusing the M2 lineup (including a heavily suspected me) looks more like evil trying to secure a fail while keeping a convenient scapegoat on the team. So I exclude the player I know is evil (Alice) and the player whose behavior most suggests being her partner (Eve), and take the most coherent good-leaning core of Diana + Bob plus myself, giving the highest chance of a fully good team based on both mission history and table talk.	[-0.034342356,-0.0066489773,-0.025729991,-0.067754105,0.036123417,0.024833301,0.019044481,0.009181425,0.008571581,0.08378689,-0.037356455,-0.011173024,0.055584975,-0.0688685,0.02575037,0.05293925,0.046076935,0.030342702,-0.010398945,0.072278,-0.080069646,-0.09396977,0.025721043,0.012501863,-0.031870767,0.061432526,0.0014425988,0.008473503,-0.0552501,-0.096505925,-0.039489977,0.034031764,0.048189238,0.035316285,-0.037026826,0.016615074,-0.03849191,-0.023327405,-0.030384654,-0.038151562,-0.007066749,-0.030924054,-0.0039781984,-0.07160137,-0.07762425,-0.0027583416,0.01597897,0.03309442,0.015063649,-0.07730237,-0.042455576,-0.0054136054,-0.032819826,0.030362938,0.011738984,0.04193551,-0.011708397,0.0718992,-0.021448132,0.049869366,0.047174286,0.05976831,-0.0053069023,0.016167602,0.07282238,0.037331473,-0.04189798,0.0035814547,-0.050202012,0.079652116,0.04069164,-0.06551192,-0.09831826,-0.11298912,-0.03642689,