430	avalon_20251201_005546	proposal	100500	Bob	good	\N	Given I know I’m good, the structure from the missions is: Mission 2’s single fail implies at least one evil in {Alice, Charlie}, and Mission 4’s single fail (with me on it and I’m good) implies at least one evil in {Diana, Eve}. That very strongly suggests the two evils are one from {Alice, Charlie} and one from {Diana, Eve}. For the final team we therefore want exactly one from each suspect pair, aiming to hit the two goods rather than the two evils.\n\nBetween Alice and Charlie, Charlie’s overall play has been more in line with cautious good behavior, while Alice has been much more aggressively tunneling me off two mixed teams. From my seat as known-good, that hard tunnel feels more like misdirection than genuine solving, so I lean Charlie as the good one in that pair.\n\nBetween Diana and Eve, Diana’s suggested core of Alice + Charlie and then choosing between herself and Eve is more consistent with someone trying to reason from the board even at the cost of excluding herself, while Eve’s push for Bob + Charlie + Eve conveniently keeps herself on the critical final team while defending me in a way that can come from either alignment. I slightly prefer Diana as the good in that pair.\n\nPutting that together, the highest-percentage good team from my perspective is me (Bob), Charlie (more likely good over Alice), and Diana (slightly more likely good over Eve).	[-0.015703306,0.010978601,0.0043609864,-0.04733595,0.018373538,0.029807722,0.020652201,0.046514373,0.03778747,0.07409221,-0.07058248,-0.03141363,0.06869189,-0.05022514,0.01473239,0.052362155,0.073260576,0.020350914,-0.0365446,0.05310478,-0.08769141,-0.11461305,0.0052242205,-0.040351808,-0.111048035,0.04494052,-0.01583843,-0.011324093,-0.022862833,-0.11901973,-0.003922685,0.049478833,0.0017862099,0.049239475,-0.029878667,0.038549166,-0.009026107,-0.016147945,0.02422608,0.008398848,-0.002927395,-0.001716285,-0.010410183,-0.03717958,-0.06899018,0.02557639,0