402	avalon_20251201_001747	proposal	100400	Diana	good	\N	Mission 2 proves that at least one of Alice or Bob must be evil, because the only difference between the successful Missions 1 and 3 (Alice+Diana) and the failed Mission 2 (Alice+Bob+Diana) is Bob joining. As Diana, I know I’m good, so the evil pair must be drawn from {Alice, Bob, Charlie, Eve} with at least one in {Alice, Bob}. If we include either Alice or Bob, we are guaranteed to have at least one highly suspicious slot on the team. By instead choosing [Diana, Charlie, Eve], we avoid the entire {Alice, Bob} set where we know evil is located, maximizing our chances that all three team members are good while also testing the untested players. This is the most logically consistent way to avoid the known danger cluster and give good the best shot at a clean success.	[0.03183562,0.013822583,-0.034894425,-0.031453565,0.05305849,0.008854023,-0.007423744,-0.014767128,0.009183189,0.04540584,-0.029156966,-0.036310438,0.11260251,-0.056370858,-0.0033127202,0.018848298,0.034648392,0.03964788,-0.003832487,-0.019885633,-0.077239536,-0.09587163,0.025542028,0.017793795,-0.069048055,0.06626435,-0.029431336,0.01572415,-0.03427153,-0.09518991,0.022521429,0.057356093,0.046661034,0.029051926,0.045294452,-0.015208388,-0.011265353,0.0076547563,0.022404341,-0.0058251936,0.003605078,-0.036603324,0.020191092,-0.054721747,-0.09255695,-0.012770238,-0.006588726,0.021929074,0.031876195,-0.07607903,-0.016469985,-0.008780268,-0.021658175,0.011975684,0.02246776,0.005478193,-0.027234482,-0.0059165307,-0.04880559,0.017010193,0.021827685,0.037773762,-0.027725017,-0.019228859,0.039265413,0.035715707,-0.039048176,0.030227546,-0.009463038,0.081519455,0.024327893,-0.010604932,-0.0658621,-0.10199112,-0.03649139,0.117432326,0.08509426,-0.026383756,0.07293902,-0.001604001,-0.0063701724,-0.08644944,0.022727322,0.11226061,0.028938396,-0.004648973,-0.062453777,-0.114549056,0.058509685,0.030611204,-0.03715264,0.00829176,0.083069086,0.09542633,0.08476575